ns0:DescribedValueSet.displayName: White Blood Cells Count Lab Test

ns0:Concept.displayName: Leukocytes [#/volume] in Blood by Automated count
Leukocytes [#/volume] in Blood by Manual count

ns0:DescribedValueSet.ns0:Purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains lab tests commonly used for a blood/serum/plasma white blood cells count test.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients with a lab test performed on a source of blood/serum/plasma for white blood cells. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element would map to Laboratory Test, Result datatype.),(Inclusion Criteria: White blood cells count lab test using the source of blood/serum/plasma with a reporting scale of number/volume.),(Exclusion Criteria: White blood cells count lab test using a non-blood/serum/plasma source of blood.)
